{{Use British English|date=October 2013}} {{BLP sources |date=July 2011}} {{Infobox person | honorific_prefix = | name = Simon McKeown | honorific_suffix = | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = 1965 | birth_place = Middlesbrough | residence = | nationality = | education = BA | alma_mater = [[University of Teesside]] | occupation = Lecturer, Artist | years_active = | employer = University of Teesside | organization = | known_for = 3D, Disability Art | home_town = [[Thirsk, North Yorkshire]] | title = [[Dadafest]] International Artist of Year 2010-2011 | term = 2010-2011 | predecessor = Pete Edwards | successor = Incumbent | boards = | awards = | website = {{official website|http://www.simon-mckeown.com/}} | footnotes = | box_width = }}
'''Simon Mckeown''' (born 1965) is a [[United Kingdom|British]] artist, and lecturer at the [[University of Teesside]]. On 4 December 2010, he was named [[DaDaFest]] Artist of the Year for 2011.{{citation needed|date=July 2017}} In 2012, he was part of the Paralympic Cultural Festival (or [[Unlimited (arts initiative)|Unlimited Festival]]), as part of a focus on Disability Arts.
